## 1. Cloud Fundamentals

- **Cloud Computing** — on-demand delivery of compute, storage, and services over the internet
- **On-demand self-service** — provision resources without human intervention
- **Elasticity** — scale resources up/down based on demand
- **Pay-as-you-go** — pay only for what you use
- **Shared responsibility model** — security split between provider and customer
- **Multi-tenancy** — shared infrastructure, isolated tenants
- **Resource pooling** — shared physical resources abstracted from users

---

## 2. Service Models

| Model | Description | You Manage | Example |
|-------|-------------|------------|---------|
| **IaaS** | Infrastructure as a Service | OS, apps, runtime | EC2, GCE, Azure VM |
| **PaaS** | Platform as a Service | Apps + data only | App Engine, App Service |
| **SaaS** | Software as a Service | Nothing (just use) | Gmail, Salesforce |
| **FaaS** | Function as a Service | Code only | Lambda, Cloud Functions |
| **CaaS** | Containers as a Service | Containers | EKS, GKE, AKS |

---

## 3. Deployment Models

- **Public Cloud** — shared, provider-owned (AWS, Azure, GCP)
- **Private Cloud** — dedicated, single-org (on-prem or hosted)
- **Hybrid Cloud** — mix of public + private
- **Multi-Cloud** — multiple public providers
- **Community Cloud** — shared by organizations with common concerns

---

## 4. Core Infrastructure

- **Region** — geographic area with multiple data centers
- **Availability Zone (AZ)** — isolated data center(s) within a region
- **Edge Location / PoP** — CDN caching points close to users
- **Data Center** — physical facility hosting infrastructure
- **Resource Group / Project** — logical container for resources

---

## 5. Networking

- **VPC / VNet** — isolated virtual network
- **Subnet** — segment of a VPC (public/private)
- **CIDR block** — IP address range notation
- **Route table** — directs network traffic
- **Internet Gateway / NAT Gateway** — internet access in/out
- **Load Balancer** — distributes traffic (L4 / L7)
- **DNS** — name resolution service
- **CDN** — content delivery / caching at the edge
- **VPN / Direct Connect** — hybrid connectivity
- **Security Group / NACL** — virtual firewalls

---

## 6. Storage

| Type | Description | Use Case |
|------|-------------|----------|
| **Object Storage** | Flat, scalable blobs | Backups, media, static sites |
| **Block Storage** | Raw volumes attached to VMs | Databases, OS disks |
| **File Storage** | Shared filesystem (NFS/SMB) | Shared app data |
| **Archive Storage** | Cold, cheap, slow retrieval | Long-term retention |

**Concepts:** durability (e.g. 11 nines), availability, replication, lifecycle policies, storage tiers, encryption at rest.

---

## 7. Compute

- **Virtual Machine (VM)** — virtualized server
- **Container** — lightweight, portable runtime unit
- **Serverless / FaaS** — event-driven, no server management
- **Spot / Preemptible instances** — cheap, interruptible capacity
- **Reserved / Committed instances** — discounted long-term commitment
- **Auto-scaling** — adjust capacity automatically

---

## 8. Scalability & Availability

- **Vertical scaling (scale up)** — bigger machine
- **Horizontal scaling (scale out)** — more machines
- **Elasticity** — automatic scaling with demand
- **High Availability (HA)** — minimal downtime via redundancy
- **Fault tolerance** — survive component failures
- **Disaster Recovery (DR)** — recovery after major failure
- **RTO** — Recovery Time Objective
- **RPO** — Recovery Point Objective
- **Redundancy** — duplicate components to avoid SPOF

---

## 9. Security & Identity

- **IAM** — Identity and Access Management
- **Principle of least privilege**
- **Roles, policies, permissions**
- **MFA** — Multi-Factor Authentication
- **Encryption** — at rest & in transit (TLS, KMS)
- **Secrets management** — secure credential storage
- **Shared responsibility model**
- **Compliance** — GDPR, HIPAA, SOC 2, ISO 27001
- **Zero Trust** — never trust, always verify

