## 10. Cost & FinOps

- **Pay-as-you-go** — usage-based billing
- **Reserved / Committed use** — discounts for commitment
- **Spot pricing** — cheap interruptible capacity
- **Cost allocation tags** — track spend by team/project
- **Right-sizing** — match resources to actual need
- **Budgets & alerts** — spending guardrails
- **TCO** — Total Cost of Ownership
- **FinOps** — cloud financial operations / cost culture

---

## 11. Architecture Principles

- **Well-Architected Framework** — operational excellence, security, reliability, performance, cost, sustainability
- **Loose coupling** — independent components
- **Statelessness** — no session state on servers
- **Immutable infrastructure** — replace, don't modify
- **Microservices** — small independent services
- **Event-driven architecture** — react to events
- **Idempotency** — safe to repeat operations
- **Design for failure** — assume things break

---

## 12. Operations & Governance

- **Infrastructure as Code (IaC)** — declarative infra (Terraform, CloudFormation)
- **Tagging strategy** — organize and track resources
- **Monitoring & logging** — observability into systems
- **Auditing** — track changes and access
- **Quotas & limits** — resource constraints
- **Landing zone** — baseline secure account/org setup
- **Policy as Code** — automated governance (OPA, SCPs)
- **Drift detection** — actual vs desired state

---

> **Quick takeaway:** The highest-leverage cloud concepts for daily DevOps work are the **shared responsibility model**, **regions/AZs for HA**, **VPC networking**, **IAM least privilege**, **auto-scaling**, and **Infrastructure as Code** — these underpin nearly every architectural decision.